Space Invaders Game
A fully functional Space Invaders game built with HTML5 Canvas and vanilla JavaScript.

Features
✅ Core Gameplay

Arrow keys to move the player ship left/right
Space bar to fire bullets
Continuous gameplay with progressive difficulty
3 lives system - game ends when lives reach 0
✅ Scoring & Progression

+100 points for each enemy destroyed
Waves increase every 500 points
Enemy spawn rate and speed increase with each wave
Top 3 high scores saved in browser localStorage
✅ Visual Polish

Retro green terminal aesthetic
Real-time HUD showing score, lives, and wave
Game Over screen with final score and ranking
Geometric shape placeholders (triangle for player, rectangles for enemies)
✅ Custom Graphics Support

Drop PNG files in the images/ folder
player-ship.png - replaces player ship geometry
enemy-ship.png - replaces enemy ship geometry
Falls back to geometric shapes if images not found
How to Play
Start: Open space_invaders.html in a web browser
Controls:
← → Arrow keys = Move
SPACE = Fire
Goal: Destroy as many enemy ships as possible before losing all 3 lives
Scoring: Each destroyed enemy = 100 points
How to Add Custom Graphics
Step 1: Create Your PNG Files
Prepare two PNG images:

player-ship.png - Your player ship (recommended: 30x30 pixels)
enemy-ship.png - Your enemy ship (recommended: 25x25 pixels)
Step 2: Add to Images Folder
Place your PNG files in the images/ folder:

space_invaders.html
images/
  ├── player-ship.png
  └── enemy-ship.png
Step 3: Reload Game
Simply refresh the page in your browser. The game will:

Load your custom images
Use them if found
Fall back to geometric shapes if images fail to load
Image Specifications
Format: PNG (transparent backgrounds recommended)
Player Ship Size: 30x30 pixels
Enemy Ship Size: 25x25 pixels
Transparency: Works best with PNG format for transparent backgrounds
Game Mechanics
Difficulty Progression
Wave 1: Enemies spawn slowly
Wave 2+: Enemies spawn faster and move quicker
New wave every 500 points
Enemy Behavior
Enemies move down and side-to-side
Enemies bounce off screen edges
Enemies fire bullets at the player
Enemies that reach the bottom disappear
Collision System
Player bullets destroy enemies (+100 points)
Enemy bullets damage player (-1 life)
Game ends when lives reach 0
High Scores
Automatically saved in browser localStorage
Persists across page refreshes
Shows top 3 scores in the sidebar
Special ranking message on game over
Technical Details
Canvas Size: 800x600 pixels
Frame Rate: 60 FPS (via requestAnimationFrame)
Storage: Browser localStorage (key: spaceInvadersHighScores)
Dependencies: None - vanilla HTML5/CSS3/JavaScript
Tips for Better Performance
Image Optimization: Keep PNG files small (< 50KB each)
Browser: Works best on modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
Clear Cache: If custom images don't appear, clear browser cache and reload
